cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper proposes a method for discovering objects in egocentric images using a convolutional neural network and object refill methodology. This involves computer vision and machine learning techniques, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of egocentric images also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques such as filtering, which could also place it in the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
